<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 12:34:36 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>背杏仁核 Neurotropin-3 降低灵长类动物的焦虑气质</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/dorsal-amygdala-neurotrophin-3-decreases-anxious-temperament-in-primates</link><description>生命早期的焦虑气质（AT）是导致焦虑、抑郁和共病药物滥用的危险因素。我们验证了早期 AT 的非人类灵长类动物模型，并将背侧杏仁核确定为 AT 神经回路的核心组成部分。在这里，我们结合 RNA 测序、病毒载体基因操作、功能性脑成像和行为表型来揭示 AT 的分子底物。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dorsal-amygdala-neurotrophin-3-decreases-anxious-temperament-in-primates2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 12:34:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/dorsal-amygdala-neurotrophin-3-decreases-anxious-temperament-in-primates</guid></item><item><title>神经发育</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/neural-development</link><description>神经发育是形成和完善神经系统的复杂的、终生的过程，从胚胎神经形成（神经管形成）开始，一直持续到成熟和重塑。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neural-development2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 12:19:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/neural-development</guid></item><item><title>研究表明，大脑原始的“恐惧中心”实际上是一个复杂的调解者</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-brains-primitive-fear-center-is-actually-a-sophisticated-mediator-research-reveals</link><description>达特茅斯学院的一项研究挑战了传统观点，即杏仁核（大脑深处参与情感、学习和决策的两侧结构）只是大脑原始的“恐惧中心”，本能地驱使我们回避我们害怕的事物，从高处和狭窄的空间到蜘蛛和人群。研究人员报告在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-brains-primitive-fear-center-is-actually-a-sophisticated-mediator-research-reveals.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 12:04:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-brains-primitive-fear-center-is-actually-a-sophisticated-mediator-research-reveals</guid></item><item><title>尺寸变化的纳米颗粒成功地将 mRNA 药物递送至胰腺</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/size-shifting-nanoparticles-successfully-deliver-mrna-medicine-to-the-pancreas</link><description>近年来，脂质纳米粒子 (mRNA-LNP) 中的 mRNA 已成为治疗多种疾病的有前途的策略，包括 COVID-19、各种癌症和慢性遗传性疾病。迄今为止，这项技术尚未成功用于胰腺疾病，但这种情况可能即将改变。在一篇论文中&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/size-shifting-nanoparticles-successfully-deliver-mrna-medicine-to-the-pancreas.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 11:49:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/size-shifting-nanoparticles-successfully-deliver-mrna-medicine-to-the-pancreas</guid></item><item><title>科学家创造出功能强大的新型铝，可以替代稀土金属</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/scientists-create-powerful-new-form-of-aluminum-that-could-replace-rare-earth-metals</link><description>研究人员发现了一种不寻常的新型铝，挑战了人们长期以来对这种常见金属行为的假设。伦敦国王学院的研究人员发现了一种不寻常的新形式的铝，它是地壳中最丰富的金属之一。这一发现指出了一个&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-create-powerful-new-form-of-aluminum-that-could-replace-rare-earth-metals.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 11:34:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/scientists-create-powerful-new-form-of-aluminum-that-could-replace-rare-earth-metals</guid></item><item><title>主观时间尺度：从人类到网络神</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/subjective-timescales-from-humans-to-cybergods</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 11:19:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/subjective-timescales-from-humans-to-cybergods</guid></item><item><title>孩子与他们的假定父亲在基因上没有关系的情况有多常见？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-often-are-children-genetically-unrelated-to-their-presumed-fathers</link><description>基因侦探发现只有 1% 的欧洲儿童有意外的亲子关系&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-often-are-children-genetically-unrelated-to-their-presumed-fathers2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 11:04:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/how-often-are-children-genetically-unrelated-to-their-presumed-fathers</guid></item><item><title>人工智能使粒子物理学超越人类的想象</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ai-takes-particle-physics-beyond-human-imagination</link><description>人工智能能否成为寻找物理标准模型中缺失部分的关键？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-takes-particle-physics-beyond-human-imagination.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 10:49:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ai-takes-particle-physics-beyond-human-imagination</guid></item><item><title>模拟显示了通往具有晶体般熵的“理想玻璃”的道路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/simulations-show-a-path-to-ideal-glass-with-crystal-like-entropy</link><description>我们在日常生活中遇到的玻璃类型，例如窗玻璃或智能手机屏幕，是无序固体。这意味着它们由锁定在适当位置的粒子组成，就像固体中的粒子一样，但随机排列，类似于它们在液体中的情况。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/simulations-show-a-path-to-ideal-glass-with-crystal-like-entropy.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 10:34:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/simulations-show-a-path-to-ideal-glass-with-crystal-like-entropy</guid></item><item><title>细胞重编程：专家综述</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cellular-reprogramming-the-expert-roundup</link><description>细胞重编程是与长寿最相关的技术之一。该领域诞生于 2006 年，当时山中伸弥 (Shinya Yamanaka) 证明，四种转录因子的混合物（通常称为 OSKM）可以导致细胞去分化和大规模再生，从而产生 iPSC（诱导多能干细胞）。大约十年后，部分重编程被证明&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cellular-reprogramming-the-expert-roundup.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 10:19:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cellular-reprogramming-the-expert-roundup</guid></item></channel></rss>